fields.summary: Prisma [Cost Update] Implement month of service

issuetype.description: Created by Jira Software - do not edit or delete. Issue type for a user story.
issuetype.name: Story

fields.description:
As a media finance user I want the month of service displayed in Ignitia to align with the flighting date in Prisma so that my invoices to the client correctly detail which month of service the client is being billed for.

*Acceptance Criteria*

*Given* a booking/placement is created in Prisma 

*When* the booking/placement is pushed to Ignitia as part of reconciliation (financial update)

*Then* The Period of Service must align with the extact dates pushed from Prisma (to allow later adjustments) and the month of service should be displayed as the Month and Year of the Start date of the Period of Service.

 

*Current Issue Background:*

Month of service is displayed properly for the first time when a new placement is created from Prisma . But after updating a placement from Prisma the MOS is not displayed correctly in Ignitia.

resolution.name: Fixed

fields.summary: Payment Schedule : Rounding issue on AR & AP amount on new payment schedule dissection.

issuetype.description: A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.
issuetype.name: Bug

fields.description:
.This issue is observed on below mentioned automation test:

*Schedule_Booking_Tax_Inclusive_Rounding*

*Issue 1)* On 3rd Applitool of automation test,

Estimate:TAX_INC_ROUND
 Vendor Buy(Tax Exclusive) : 135.92
 Markup: 0
 Client rate card cost(Buy): 135.92
 Buy Nominal Tax rate: 10.363
 Sell Nominal Tax rate: 10.363
 Vendor cost to Agency(Buy): 135.92
 Client cost to client(Buy): 135.92
 Cost to client(Buy): 135.92

Sell nominal tax(buy) = Cost to client(buy) * 0.10363 = 135.92*0.10363 = 14.085 == Rounded to 14.09
 AR(Buy)= Cost to client(Buy) + Sell nominal tax(Buy) = 135.92+14.09 = {color:#FF0000}150.01{color}

As per booking AR(Buy) should be 150, hence {color:#FF0000}0.01{color} rounding issue is present in payment schedule dissection.

Similarly for AP(Buy) also same rounding issue is observed. 
 Please find attached screenshot for the same.

*Issue 2)* On 4th Applitool of automation test

When currency is 'Buy to Base' in payment schedule dissection then, AP amount on rate tab is 300 but on payment schedule dissection it is {color:#FF0000}300.01{color}

*Issue 3)*

Scenario: Schedule_Booking_Tax_Inclusive_Rounding
	Given I Delete All Bookings from Schedule 'TAX_INC_ROUND'
	Given I am at 'Media/Schedule/Edit/9886?tab=Cinema'
	#Create bookings
	When I Create Default Booking for Tax Inclusive Rounding
	When I Check booking row "1" to 'true'
	Then I duplicate the booking on Job Media Type 'Cinema'
	When I update Booking Date to '01-01-2017'
	Then I navigate to booking details Rate Tab of 'Cinema'	
	Then I Enter Vendor Commission % '0'
	When I click Save Angular
	When I open Applitools Eyes for 'Schedule_Booking_Tax_Inclusive_Rounding'
	#Applitools set no.1 - 1st booking - Rate tab
	When I select booking row "1"	
	Then I navigate to booking details Rate Tab of 'Cinema'
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	When I click pagedown for Rate Schedule tab
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	#Applitools image no.3 - 1st booking - Payment Schedule tab - Buy Currency
	Then I navigate to booking details Payment Schedule of 'Cinema'
	When I select Vendor Payment Buy Currency
	When I select Client Billing Buy Currency	
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	#Applitools image no.4 - 1st booking - Payment Schedule tab - Buy/Sell To Base Currency
	When I select Vendor Payment Buy to Base Currency
	When I select Client Billing Sell to Base Currency
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	#Applitools image no.5 - 1st booking - Payment Schedule tab - Sell Currency
	When I select Client Billing Sell Currency
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	#Applitools set no.6 - 2nd booking - Rate tab
	When I select booking row "2"	
	Then I navigate to booking details Rate Tab of 'Cinema'
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	When I click pagedown for Rate Schedule tab
	Then I Verify UI with Applitools
	#Applitools image no.8 - 2nd booking - Payment Schedule tab - Buy Currency - Even Monthly

	Then I Reallocate payment using 'Even monthly'
	When I click Save Angular
	When I select Vendor Payment Buy Currency
	When I select Client Billing Buy Currency

	When I select Client Billing Sell to Base Currency
